# Audric-Side Context Assembly

Companion to `t2000/.cursor/rules/memory-injection-architecture.mdc`. That rule documents the **engine-side wiring contract** (the 5-layer ordering when a host configures `EngineConfig.memoryStore` and calls `engine.submitMessage`). This rule documents the **audric-side content builders** that feed those layers in `apps/web-v2/app/api/chat/route.ts`.

**Architecture note (post-v0.7e Phase 5):** web-v2 does NOT call `engine.submitMessage`. It composes AI SDK v6's `Experimental_Agent` directly with engine TOOLS (`toAISDKTools`). The 5-layer engine contract maps onto a simpler 3-surface audric architecture:

| Surface on `Agent` | Audric content | Engine-rule mapping |
|---|---|---|
| `instructions` (static) | `buildAudricSystemPrompt({ ... })` | Layer 1 (base) + AdviceLog block — folded together at construction time. (Engine layer 2 `<financial_context>` was retired in S.375; Audric supplies no block.) |
| `prepareStep` (dynamic per turn) | `buildMemoryPrepareStep({ ... })` | Layer 3 (`<memory_recall>`). MemWal `recall(latestUserMessage)` returns top-K records → injected into `system` for that step. |
| `onFinish` (dynamic post-turn) | `buildMemoryWriteCallback({ ... })` | Layer 3 write side. MemWal `analyze()` extracts new facts from the completed turn and persists. |

There is no audric-side analog to engine layer 4 (`skillRecipeBlock`) — skills are exposed as MCP prompts to external LLM consumers (Claude Desktop / Cursor), not injected into Audric chat's system prompt. See `t2000/.cursor/rules/tool-surface-topology.mdc` for the skill ↔ MCP wiring.

## The content builders

Every layer's content comes from one canonical helper. Don't fork.

| Helper | File | What it produces | When it runs |
|---|---|---|---|
| `buildAudricSystemPrompt` | `apps/web-v2/lib/audric/system-prompt.ts` | The static `instructions` string fed to `new Agent({ instructions })`. Composes base prompt + `<advice_log>` (last 30 days) + recipe / persona content. | Once per request, in chat route phase 9. |
| `buildAdviceContext` | `apps/web-v2/lib/audric/moat-context.ts` | Last 30 days of `AdviceLog` rows hydrated as a context block; lets the agent stay consistent with prior recommendations. | Inside `buildAudricSystemPrompt` (folded into `instructions`). |
| `MemWalMemoryStore` | `apps/web-v2/lib/audric/memwal-memory-store.ts` | The adapter that bridges the engine's `MemoryStore` interface to the founder-owned `@mysten-incubation/memwal` SDK. Exposes `recall(query)` + `analyze(turn)` + `forget(id)` per the SDK contract. | Constructed once per request. Used by `prepareStep` + `onFinish`. |
| `buildMemoryPrepareStep` | `apps/web-v2/lib/audric/memwal-prepare-step.ts` | Returns the `prepareStep` callback. Per turn: calls `memoryStore.recall(latestUserMessage)`, formats top-K hits into `<memory_recall>`, returns `{ system: prependedSystem }`. Falls back gracefully (empty layer) when recall throws or returns 0 records. | Once per turn (AI SDK calls `prepareStep` before each step). |
| `buildMemoryWriteCallback` | `apps/web-v2/lib/audric/memwal-write-callback.ts` | Returns the `onFinish` callback. Post turn: calls `memoryStore.analyze({ messages, response })` so MemWal extracts new facts and persists them under the user's namespace. | Once per turn (AI SDK calls `onFinish` after the response stream completes). |

## The Agent construction (single source of truth)

```typescript
// apps/web-v2/app/api/chat/route.ts ~line 1195
const audricAgent = new Agent({
  model,                                  // gateway('anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6')
  tools,                                  // toAISDKTools(engineTools, ctx)
  instructions: systemInstructions,       // buildAudricSystemPrompt({...}) — static, contains layers 1+2+advice
  prepareStep: prepareStepCallback,       // buildMemoryPrepareStep({...}) — dynamic, layer 3
  onFinish: writeCallback,                // buildMemoryWriteCallback({...}) — dynamic, layer 3 write
  stopWhen: stepCountIs(DEFAULT_MAX_TURNS),
  experimental_telemetry: experimentalTelemetry,
  experimental_context: internalContext,
});
```

Every audric-side context concern routes through one of these 5 inputs (`instructions`, `tools`, `prepareStep`, `onFinish`, `experimental_context`). Don't add context layers anywhere else.

## What's banned

```typescript
// ❌ Static `instructions` that tries to inject memory
const instructions = `${baseSystem}\n\n${memoryBlock}`;
// Memory recall is per-turn — must come from prepareStep, not the static instructions.

// ❌ Reaching for deleted Prisma models
import { UserFinancialProfile, UserMemory, ChainFact, UserFinancialContext } from '@/lib/prisma';
// UserFinancialProfile / UserMemory / ChainFact dropped in S.221 + S.254;
// UserFinancialContext dropped in S.375. MemWal is the long-term memory store;
// fresh financial state comes from read tools, not a snapshot.

// ❌ Re-introducing a pre-injected financial-context block
const wallet = await getPortfolio(...);
const block = `<financial_context>...${wallet}...</financial_context>`;
// The daily snapshot was retired in S.375. Don't pre-inject balances —
// let the LLM call balance_check / savings_info / rates_info for fresh state.

// ❌ Mixing static `system` and per-turn `prepareStep` content for the same layer
const agent = new Agent({
  instructions: '...with a memory block...',
  prepareStep: () => ({ system: '...with a memory block...' }), // double-injection
});

// ❌ Adding a 6th surface on Agent
const agent = new Agent({
  instructions, tools, prepareStep, onFinish,
  experimental_some_other_layer: ..., // STOP. Use one of the 5 existing surfaces.
});
```

## Adding a new context layer

Most "I need the LLM to know X" concerns fold into existing layers. Decide:

- **Static fact about the user** (preferences, persona, account-age policy) → fold into `buildAudricSystemPrompt` (the `instructions` builder).
- **Dynamic fact derived from the turn's user message** (relevant memory, similar past turns) → extend `buildMemoryPrepareStep`. MemWal handles vector retrieval.
- **Fact known at chat-time but expensive to compute** (advice log, portfolio totals) → pre-build offline or in a cron, store in Prisma, hydrate via a helper called from `buildAudricSystemPrompt` (matches the `AdviceLog` + `PortfolioSnapshot` patterns).
- **Tool-driven fact** (the result of a read tool the LLM should call) → don't pre-inject. Let the LLM call the tool. The agent harness is designed for this.

If none of those apply, you probably don't need a context layer — push back on the requirement.

